CrudPickerPanel
public class PickerPanel<B extends Serializable>
extends ListTablePanel<B>

Basic ServicePanel that shows a List of objects and allows the user to pick one of them. This panel requires one CallbackAction that is executed when the user requests to go back and one CallbackAction that is executed when the user selects an object from the list. If the itemSelectedAction is null, the select button is not shown. This is useful only in the context of a CrudPickerPanel. A plain PickerPanel does not have much use when the user can't pick anything.
